<br>
The guild rotation thing, this is different. With the outstanding usefullness of the cleric epic, every cleric who is able to muster the support should get a shot at this. How the hell would you do a guild rotation? Suppose a cleric in a tiny guild with tons and tons of friends wants in? Guildless? Suppose a few clerics from the same guild are ready at once, in a rotation of 6 guilds. That next cleric has to wait behind 5 other people. The day after that second cleric is ready, What if guild #7 has a cleric ready and demonstrated the support to kill Ragefire (an extremely easy creature) Well, that guild needs to be let in, assuming that the 2nd cleric in the first guild gets bumped one place back. Is that fair to that second cleric? After all, that cleric was ready first. What if a guild has 3 clerics ready at once, and 2 more guilds become ready after that, each with 2 clerics. Well, that 3rd cleric in the first guild just got screwed.<br>
<br>
Another thing, whatever your feelings may be, you can not argue with this system's efficiency. Most servers get maybe 1-2 epics a week if they are lucky (why organize a raid to kill Naggy in order to kill Rage, when your camp is only going to get stolen from you...again.) we do not lose Ragefires from silly conflicts. For Luclin, only 1 epic in a week is a pretty bad week. We have a backlog of about a dozen or so people? HAHAHA!!! Most servers have backlogs of like 30! I even heard of a server with about 50 clerics waiting for Ragefire!<br>
<br>
The important thing is, that the clerics of Luclin mostly agree with this system, and if blame could be pinned onto one entity for breaking this, and sending us into a paranoid militaristic staking out of Ragefire, and fights over the spawn, the backlash against that entity would be hellish. <br>
<br>
You can live without a few people or guilds. Everyone needs resses. <p>Cayleu Starshine
