<br>
When I became ready for Ragefire, I was placed 3rd from the bottom of a long list. I was 12th on the list, and yet, in what seemed like no time at all, I have my epic. (yay!) I didn't complain when I was number 12. Oh btw, I GUARANTEE I would have been 15th on the list if there were 3 more clerics ready at the time. 20th if there were 8 more clerics ready.<br>
6 Apex clerics were added to the _bottom_ because 6 were ready and Apex clerics were low priority since so many already had their epic. There's no conspiracy about it. In fact, the list was definitely NOT in Apex's favor. But that seems fair to me, and so it is.<br>
<br>
Dorrian (who wouldn't have been ready for Ragefire if Apex had not _CoH'd_ him in to loot the Overking's corpse) was placed _above_ Apex clerics who were ready for Ragefire before he was. Why? Because in general, most of us aren't unaware of the fact that Heroes is almost singlehandedly responsible for 15+ of the clerics on the server having their epics in such a short time. We thought Dorrian (and Heroes) deserved a cleric epic. I didn't curse him for being put ahead of me. Instead I helped him kill Ragefire, thus speeding up the list's movement.<br>
<br>
The cleric community on this server understands why this list makes sense, and LoS wasn't complaining when their only ready cleric at the time was put near the top of the list. He could easily have been put after our 6 apex clerics. The bottom line is that Ragefire spawns on average 2 times per week if we're diligent about killing Naggy. Waiting an extra month to get your epic is SO WORTH IT when you know you won't get KS'd, when you KNOW your turn is coming and you're GOING to get your epic, rather than all of our guilds fighting over who gets it next and having people have to start over.<br>
<br>
This list is the most intelligent way of handling it that I've seen yet. It shows who was ready first, therefore meaning that if I've been ready a month longer than you, I'll get mine first. That's how it should be.<br>
