<br>
When I first started organizing and running dragon raids again, I did it to help people get their epic items.  Books for paladins, scales for bards and warriors.  The rest of the look was just a side item.  I didn't start them to deliberately spawn Ragefire for clerics, although I have no problem doing so.  I want you to get your epics just as much as I want to get mine.<br>
<br>
However, I don't like basically being told &quot;either you get your raid together now and kill Nagafen instead of in two days, or we kill him now and you don't get to have your raid period.&quot;  It's one thing if someone has a raid planned almost an entire week after he spawns.  Two or three days is another matter entirely.  See, there's certain bards, paladins, and warriors in invite on these raids every time.  That's because they've been with me everytime fighting for their epic just like I am.  When a raid gets forced to shift timeframes massively, it screws that up, and it also causes a lot more hassle/confusion/scrabbling for people.<br>
<br>
So yes, I can understand why clerics want Nagafen dead as soon as he pops.  But put bluntly, I personally won't be moving any more raids up.  If I schedule one for Friday, that's because I have already organized the people to be READY to kill him on Friday, and that's when the people who've worked just as hard for their epic as any cleric has will be ready to kill him as well.  As it was I had to walk out on the Naggy raid that was done this week because it was moved up, and I don't have forever and a day on the weekdays to kill a dragon.  I have no idea if scales dropped, and I deliberately haven't asked because I'll probably get very pissed off if one did.<br>
<br>
If you can respect that, that's fine.  It'd be very nice of you.  If you can't respect that and take the stance of &quot;cleric epics are more important than anyone else's epic&quot;, then don't bother contacting me to help again.  As you've said yourself, epics are FOR THE PERSON OBTAINING THEM.  They are a personal measure of satisfaction that you completed a long and difficult quest.  Other epics are no different, except that the effects and usefulness of them varies.  Other classes want their epic just as much as you want yours.<br>
<br>
So other than that, I'll be happy to kill Nagafen every week for you, provided someone else doesn't have a raid scheduled.  <br>
<br>
